&lt;snip&gt;

I think we all broadly agree that there is no single formula for a good
paper and you and Jeff are arguing more about matters of degree. I am very
interested in this subject as you know and I think it merits a lot more
attention than it usually gets, which is one reason I&#39;m glad you got deeper
into it. So here I want to add some more weight to the case for qualitative
papers. I should warn everyone up front that I took this opportunity
basically to write an essay, so this is a long post full of my thoughts on
this issue.

I believe most people in our field would agree with JBM&#39;s assertion that
there is &quot;a strong correlation between weak papers and papers without strong
quantitative results.&quot;



